<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 06 at 2:50PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Wheeler
County through 315 PM EDT...
At 249 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Little Ocmulgee State
Park, or near McRae. This storm was nearly stationary.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Alamo, Scotland and Little Ocmulgee State Park.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
